SSE Streaming Flow
From CLAUDE.md:411-418:

python
# 1. Create SSE queue at request start
queue = asyncio.Queue()
set_request_sse_queue(queue)

# 2. Return StreamingResponse immediately
return StreamingResponse(sse_generator(queue), media_type="text/event-stream")

# 3. Background task sends messages
send_request_via_sse_queue(event="chunk", data={"text": "..."})
send_request_via_sse_queue(event="text", data={"message": "..."})
send_request_via_sse_queue(event="done", data={})

# 4. Put None to signal completion
queue.put(None)  # Closes SSE connection
Event Types:

chunk - LLM streaming chunks
text - Final text response
collect_inputs - Request user input
tool_response - Tool execution result
done - Conversation turn complete
Key Architectural Patterns
1. Request Context Pattern
Thread-local storage for cache client, instance_id, SSE queue
Available anywhere via get_request_*() functions
Cleared at request end
2. State Management Pattern
ExecutionPlan (conversation-level) → ExecutionTask (step-level)
Parent-child hierarchy for workflows
Persisted to cache for multi-turn continuity
3. Pipeline Pattern
Sequential stage execution: START → ... → FINISH
Each stage: execute() → next_stage()
Resumable via resume_execution_stage
4. Cache-First Pattern
Check cache before calling ServiceNow/Glide
TTL-based expiration
Fallback to API on cache miss
5. Async State Lock Pattern
From cache_client.py:430-526:

python
# Prevent race conditions during async tool execution
acquire_async_state_lock(cache_client, conversation_id)
# ... update state ...
release_async_state_lock(cache_client, conversation_id)
Summary
Architecture: Multi-layered with LBF Client → Conversation Server → Agent Orchestrator → Cache/Mosaic/ServiceNow

Call Flow: SSE streaming with background pipeline execution, state persisted to cache between turns

Cache: Redis-backed via Central Cache Service, instance-scoped, used for skills, state, properties, attachments, and translations
